section(class="mb-8 max-w-lg grid gap-4")
    h1(class="mt-12 text-4xl font-medium font-title dark:text-white")
        | I study CS and public policy at Berkeley, and I’m working towards truly personal computing.
    p I’m passionate about the future of coding, tools that make it fun and easy to build tools, and calm technology that helps us achieve our goals.
    p I like compilers, the web, and good design.

include /subscribe
p(class="mt-1.5 text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400") Or follow on #[a(href="https://twitter.com/KabirGoel" class="border-b") Twitter]
section(class="mt-12")
    h2(class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-4")
        span(class="font-semibold") Recently
        span(class="border-t flex-1")
    div(class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 markdown")
        ul
            li Fostering Berkeley’s startup ecosystem through #[a(href="https://thefuture.build" class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300") Build&nbsp;the&nbsp;Future] and #[a(href="https://berkeleydemo.day" class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300") Berkeley&nbsp;Demo&nbsp;Day].
            li Working at #[a(href="https://pynecone.io" class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300") Pynecone], a startup making it possible to write full-stack apps in just Python.
            li Finishing up my tenure as VP of Projects and low-code guy at #[a(href="https://calblueprint.org" class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300") Cal&nbsp;Blueprint], a student org that builds digital systems to promote public welfare.
            li Researching better ways to build web apps using reactive models like spreadsheets and notebooks. A tool I call #[a(href="https://twitter.com/KabirGoel/status/1643868228865916928" class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300") Smoothie] is slowly taking shape through this research.
div(class="space-y-12 mt-12")
    each yearWithPosts in collections.postsByYear.slice().reverse()
        - const [year, yearPosts] = yearWithPosts
        section
            h2(class="flex items-center space-x-4 mb-8")
                span(class="font-semibold")= year
                span(class="border-t flex-1")
            div(class="grid gap-6 max-w-screen-sm")
                each post in yearPosts.slice().reverse()
                    a(href=post.url, class="grid group gap-1")
                        h3(class="leading-tight text-lg font-semibold text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 group-hover:text-amber-500 dark:group-hover:text-yellow-500 transition-colors") #{post.data.title}
                        p(class="text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400")= post.data.subtitle
                        p(class="text-gray-500 dark:text-zinc-400 font-sans whitespace-nowrap text-sm")= filters.readableDate(post.date).split(' ').slice(0, ).join(' ')
